BooleanUtils.toBoolean() - invalid drop-thru in case statement causes StringIndexOutOfBoundsException
The method BooleanUtils.toBoolean() has a case statement; case 3 drops through to case 4; this can cause StringIndexOutOfBoundsException, for example with the test: assertEquals(false, BooleanUtils.toBoolean("tru")); The end of case 3 should return false. Patch to follow for source and unit test.